.TH NodeFactories 3 "Last change: 29 August 2005" "Release 0.5" "Ulm's Oberon System"
.SH NAME
NodeFactories \- persistent objects that construct \fINames.Node\fP objects
.SH SYNOPSIS
.Pg
TYPE Factory = POINTER TO FactoryRec;
TYPE FactoryRec = RECORD (PersistentDisciplines.ObjectRec) END;
.sp 0.7
TYPE ConstructNodeProc = PROCEDURE (factory: Factory;
                                    VAR node: Names.Node) : BOOLEAN;
TYPE Interface = POINTER TO InterfaceRec;
TYPE InterfaceRec =
   RECORD
      (Objects.ObjectRec)
      constructNode: ConstructNodeProc;
   END;
.sp 0.7
PROCEDURE Init(factory: Factory; if: Interface);
PROCEDURE ConstructNode(factory: Factory; VAR node: Names.Node) : BOOLEAN;
.Pe
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I NodeFactories
is an interface for persistent factory objects that allow to construct
objects of type \fINames.Node\fP. Factories allow to separate the
decision what kind of extension of \fINames.Node\fP is to be created with
which parameters from the actual creation. In the context of \fINames(3)\fP
and name services, factories allow to re-create regular nodes and links
to other name services after a reboot of the name service.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.Tb Names(3)
.Tp Names(3)
abstraction for name hierarchies
.Te
